#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:4
msgid "Configuring NGINX with SSL and HTTP/2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:6
msgid ""
"Using SSL gives greater security by ensuring that communications between "
"Mattermost clients and the Mattermost server are encrypted. It also "
"allows you to configure NGINX to use the HTTP/2 protocol."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:8
msgid ""
"Although you can configure HTTP/2 without SSL, both Firefox and Chrome "
"browsers support HTTP/2 on secure connections only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:10
msgid ""
"You can use any certificate that you want, but these instructions show "
"you how to download and install certificates from `Let's Encrypt "
"<https://letsencrypt.org/>`__, a free certificate authority."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:13
msgid ""
"If Let’s Encrypt is enabled, forward port 80 through a firewall, with "
"`Forward80To443 <https://docs.mattermost.com/administration/config-"
"settings.html#forward-port-80-to-443>`__ ``config.json`` setting set to "
"``true`` to complete the Let’s Encrypt certification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:15
msgid "**To configure SSL and HTTP/2:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:17
msgid "Log in to the server that hosts NGINX and open a terminal window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:18
msgid "Install git."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:20
msgid "If you are using Ubuntu or Debian:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:22
msgid "``sudo apt-get install git``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:24
msgid "If you are using RHEL:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:26
msgid "``sudo yum install git``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:28
msgid "Clone the Let's Encrypt repository on GitHub."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:30
msgid "``git clone https://github.com/letsencrypt/letsencrypt``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:32
msgid "Change to the ``letsencrypt`` directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:34
msgid "``cd letsencrypt``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:36
msgid "Stop NGINX."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:38
#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:107
msgid "On Ubuntu 14.04 and RHEL 6:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:40
msgid "``sudo service nginx stop``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:42
#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:111
msgid "On Ubuntu 16.04, Ubuntu 18.04 and RHEL 7:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:44
msgid "``sudo systemctl stop nginx``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:46
msgid "Run ``netstat`` to make sure that nothing is listening on port 80."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:48
msgid "``netstat -na | grep ':80.*LISTEN'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:50
msgid "Run the Let's Encrypt installer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:52
msgid "``./letsencrypt-auto certonly --standalone``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:54
msgid ""
"When prompted, enter your domain name. After the installation is "
"complete, you can find the certificate in the   ``/etc/letsencrypt/live``"
" directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:56
msgid ""
"Open the file ``/etc/nginx/sites-available/mattermost`` as root in a text"
" editor and update the *server* section to incorporate the highlighted "
"lines in the following sample. Make sure to replace *{domain-name}* with "
"your own domain name, in 3 places."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:105
msgid "Restart NGINX."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:109
msgid "``sudo service nginx start``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:113
msgid "``sudo systemctl start nginx``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:115
msgid "Check that your SSL certificate is set up correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:117
msgid ""
"Test the SSL certificate by visiting a site such as "
"https://www.ssllabs.com/ssltest/index.html"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:118
msgid ""
"If there’s an error about the missing chain or certificate path, there is"
" likely an intermediate certificate missing that needs to be included."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:120
msgid ""
"Configure ``cron`` so that the certificate will automatically renew every"
" month."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:122
msgid "``crontab -e``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:124
msgid ""
"In the following line, use your own domain name in place of *{domain-"
"name}*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/config-ssl-http2-nginx.rst:126
msgid ""
"``@monthly /home/ubuntu/letsencrypt/letsencrypt-auto certonly --reinstall"
" --nginx -d {domain-name} && sudo service nginx reload``"
msgstr ""

